cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with language modeling in the context of dialog. Additionally, the use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) for modeling the interactions between speakers in a dialog suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The focus on improving language modeling performance also suggests that the paper may be relevant to the sub-category of cs.SD (Sound) as dialog is an auditory form of communication. Finally, the use of RNNs for language modeling suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
